prod_01KPDJ5JPHP42MHRZMNRG25XPN	Tiger Eye Bracelet	in0004	\N	Do you frequently experience the disturbing emotions of fear and anxiety? Struggling to navigate through life's challenges? Discover the transformative power of a Tiger's Eye Bracelet.\n\nMystical and powerful, the Tiger’s Eye is hailed as the “all-seeing all-knowing eye,” believed to grant the wearer increased perception. Traditionally, it is recognized as a symbol of prosperity and good fortune, safeguarding the wearer's resources and deflecting potential threats from others.\n\nNamed for its resemblance to a cat’s eye, this captivating stone boasts a brown/yellow base and a luminous golden-yellow shimmer, imparting a touch of fascination and elegance.\n\nKindly note that images are just a graphical representation of crystals. Size, Shape and Colour may vary at the time of delivery.\n\n---\n\n1) Tiger’s Eye combines properties that promote vitality.\n2) Tiger’s Eye is prepared to protect, sharpening one’s inner vision.\n3) It may assist you in changing your perspective to view obstacles as challenges rather than setbacks.\n4) Empower you to move past fear and build up your courage.\n5)Tiger’s Eye helps you remember that you can accomplish whatever you put your mind to.\n\n---\n\n▶Tiger's eye bracelet is composed of quartz with intergrown amphibole fibers that have been converted to golden or rusty-brown limonite.\n\nNote:\n\n1)Crack-like lines, fissures, uneven texture, or beads and crystals are natural.\n\n2)If a crystal breaks or snaps in half or pieces, or sometimes could break while in transport … it does not affect the quality of the crystal. Crystals are naturally brittle and a broken crystal just means now you have more than one piece. Any crystal piece you have is any way broken from a larger chunk.\n\n3)In case your bracelet, pendant, or ring feels like it’s not your size, feel free to transfer them in a new string or to get them re-made with a jeweler.	f	published	https://backend.pragyavijh.com/static/1776424241705-IN0004.png	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	2026-04-17 11:10:41.873+00	2026-04-17 11:10:41.873+00	\N	{"ingredients": "▶Tiger's eye bracelet is composed of quartz with intergrown amphibole fibers that have been converted to golden or rusty-brown limonite.\\n\\nNote:\\n\\n1)Crack-like lines, fissures, uneven texture, or beads and crystals are natural.\\n\\n2)If a crystal breaks or snaps in half or pieces, or sometimes could break while in transport … it does not affect the quality of the crystal. Crystals are naturally brittle and a broken crystal just means now you have more than one piece. Any crystal piece you have is any way broken from a larger chunk.\\n\\n3)In case your bracelet, pendant, or ring feels like it’s not your size, feel free to transfer them in a new string or to get them re-made with a jeweler.", "inventory_id": "IN0004"}
