de with a jeweler.	f	published	https://backend.pragyavijh.com/static/1776424250128-IN0020.png	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	2026-04-17 11:10:50.303+00	2026-04-17 11:10:50.303+00	\N	{"ingredients": "Green Aventurine is a variety of quartz characterized by its green color, which is typically due to the presence minerals such as chlorite within the stone. Green Aventurine often exhibits a shimmering or sparkling effect known as aventurescence, caused by reflective inclusions of mica or other minerals.\\n\\nAbout the Product\\n\\n1-Crack-like lines, fissures, uneven texture or beads and crystals are natural.\\n\\n2-If a crystal breaks or snaps in half or in pieces, or sometimes could break while in transport … it does not affect the quality of the crystal. Crystals are naturally brittle and a broken crystal just means now you have more than one piece. Any crystal piece you have is any way broken from a larger chunk.\\n\\n3-In case your bracelet, pendant, or ring feels like it’s not your size, feel free to transfer them in a new string or to get them re-made with a jeweler.", "inventory_id": "IN0020"}
